modules.name: Foreign.Object
modules.comments:
This module defines a type of native homogeneous Javascript Objects.

To maximize performance, Javascript objects are not wrapped,
and some native code is used even when it's not necessary.

declarations.comments: `Object a` represents a homogeneous JS Object with values of type `a`.
declarations.title: Object

declarations.comments: An empty map
declarations.title: empty

declarations.comments: Test whether a map is empty
declarations.title: isEmpty

declarations.comments: Calculate the number of key/value pairs in a map
declarations.title: size

declarations.comments: Create an `Object a` with one key/value pair
declarations.title: singleton

declarations.comments: Insert or replace a key/value pair in a map
declarations.title: insert

declarations.comments: Lookup the value for a key in a map
declarations.title: lookup

declarations.comments: Unfolds a map into a list of key/value pairs
declarations.title: toUnfoldable

declarations.comments:
Unfolds a map into a list of key/value pairs which is guaranteed to be
sorted by key
declarations.title: toAscUnfoldable

declarations.comments: Create an `Object a` from a foldable collection of key/value pairs
declarations.title: fromFoldable

declarations.comments:
Create an `Object a` from a foldable collection of key/value pairs, using the
specified function to combine values for duplicate keys.
declarations.title: fromFoldableWith

declarations.comments:
Create an `Object a` from a homogeneous record, i.e. all of the record
fields are of the same type.
declarations.title: fromHomogeneous

declarations.comments: Delete a key and value from a map
declarations.title: delete

declarations.comments:
Delete a key and value from a map, returning the value
as well as the subsequent map
declarations.title: pop

declarations.comments: Test whether a `String` appears as a key in a map
declarations.title: member

declarations.comments: Insert, remove or update a value for a key in a map
declarations.title: alter

declarations.comments: Remove or update a value for a key in a map
declarations.title: update

declarations.comments: Apply a function of two arguments to each key/value pair, producing a new map
declarations.title: mapWithKey

declarations.comments:
Filter out those key/value pairs of a map for which a predicate
fails to hold.
declarations.title: filterWithKey

declarations.comments:
Filter out those key/value pairs of a map for which a predicate
on the key fails to hold.
declarations.title: filterKeys

declarations.comments:
Filter out those key/value pairs of a map for which a predicate
on the value fails to hold.
declarations.title: filter

declarations.comments: Get an array of the keys in a map
declarations.title: keys

declarations.comments: Get a list of the values in a map
declarations.title: values

declarations.comments:
Compute the union of two maps, preferring the first map in the case of
duplicate keys.
declarations.title: union

declarations.comments: Compute the union of a collection of maps
declarations.title: unions

declarations.comments: Test whether one map contains all of the keys and values contained in another map
declarations.title: isSubmap

declarations.comments: Fold the keys and values of an object
declarations.title: fold

declarations.comments:
Fold the keys and values of an object, accumulating values using some
`Monoid`.
declarations.title: foldMap

declarations.comments:
Fold the keys and values of an object, accumulating values and effects in
some `Monad`.
declarations.title: foldM

declarations.comments:
Fold the keys and values of a map.

This function allows the folding function to terminate the fold early,
using `Maybe`.
declarations.title: foldMaybe

declarations.comments: Test whether all key/value pairs in a `Object` satisfy a predicate.
declarations.title: all

declarations.comments: Convert an immutable Object into a mutable Object
declarations.title: thawST

declarations.comments: Convert a mutable Object into an immutable Object
declarations.title: freezeST

declarations.comments:
Freeze a mutable Object, creating an immutable Object. Use this function as you would use
`ST.run` to freeze a mutable reference.

The rank-2 type prevents the Object from escaping the scope of `runST`.
declarations.title: runST

declarations.comments: Generates a `Object` using the specified key and value generators.
declarations.title: genForeignObject

modules.name: Foreign.Object.ST
modules.comments:
Helper functions for working with mutable objects using the `ST` effect.

This module can be used when performance is important and mutation is a
local effect.

declarations.comments:
A reference to a mutable object

The first type parameter represents the memory region which the map belongs
to. The second type parameter defines the type of elements of the mutable
object.

The runtime representation of a value of type `STObject r a` is the same as
that of `Object a`, except that mutation is allowed.
declarations.title: STObject

declarations.comments: Create a new, empty mutable object
declarations.title: new

declarations.comments: Get the value for a key in a mutable object
declarations.title: peek

declarations.comments: Update the value for a key in a mutable object
declarations.title: poke

declarations.comments: Remove a key and the corresponding value from a mutable object
declarations.title: delete

declarations.comments:
Unsafely get the object out of ST without copying it

If you later change the ST version of the map the pure value will also change.
declarations.title: unsafeFreeze

declarations.comments:
Unsafely get the value for a key in a object.

This function does not check whether the key exists in the object.
declarations.title: unsafeIndex
